      "content": "i feel like some historians say that the nonviolent approach was actually kind of a distraction from more radical groups that were doing the real work of making the government sweat. like, was the \"moral awareness\" u mentioned actually the driving force, or was it just people being afraid of the more militant groups at the time?",
